title: Readout of the Vice President’s Call with Australian Foreign Minister Julie Bishop – The White House
content:
Statements & Releases			

		Foreign Policy	

Issued on:
January 26, 2017
Today, Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Australian Foreign Minister Julie Bishop. Foreign Minister Bishop congratulated the Vice President on the inauguration. The Vice President thanked Foreign Minister Bishop for Australia’s steadfast partnership and contributions around the globe. The two reaffirmed the importance of continuing to strengthen the U.S.-Australia alliance to maintain peace and security in the region.
